The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Piramal sells diagnostic arm 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Piramal sells diagnostic arm 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, July 14: Piramal Healthcare Ltd is selling its subsidiary Piramal Diagnostic Services Ltd to Super Religare Laboratories Ltd in an all-cash deal worth Rs 600 crore.        
	Piramal Diagnostic Services Ltd (PDSL) provides pathology and radiology diagnostic services through a network of 107 laboratories and had revenues of over Rs 200 crore in 2009-10.         
	After the acquisition, Super Religare Laboratories (SRL) will have the largest network of pathology and radiology centres and become the leader in the diagnostic services industry in the country. Piramal Healthcare (Piramal) will continue to be involved in the business, including representation on the board of directors and the executive committee of SRL.        
	Piramal will receive an upfront payment of Rs 300 crore from SRL for the diagnostic services business. The rest will come over a period of three years.        
	The combined entity will have nearly 170 laboratories and 1,500 collection centres and will serve more than 12 million customers annually. According to Piramal, the deal will benefit both the entities as it will have SRLs reach and brand recognition, which will be complemented by PDSLs processes and systems, pool of doctors and a robust integrated service model covering both pathology and radiology.                                                                                                                                                                
